humanMachineDialogue.author: Memory Reasoning
humanMachineDialogue.text: The report indicates that there was one sentinel lymph node assessed and it was negative for metastatic carcinoma (Rule 8, New Rules 10 and 11). There is no information about metastases in regional lymph nodes. Therefore, the N stage is N0.

humanMachineDialogue.author: ZS Reasoning
humanMachineDialogue.text: The report indicates that the sentinel lymph node (specimen A) was negative for metastatic carcinoma by both H&E and immunostains. This means that there is no evidence of cancer in the lymph nodes. The N stage is determined by the presence and extent of cancer in the lymph nodes. In this case, since there is no cancer found in the lymph nodes, the N stage would be N0.
